Sentencas: Oxygen reduction reaction in a double perovskite material, PrBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.5Fe0.5O5+delta (PBSCF), was studied for application as a cathode in a solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC).
Titulo: Identifying the Origin of the Limiting Process in a Double Perovskite PrBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.5Fe0.5O5+δ Thin-Film Electrode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Electrochemical measurements were performed on a geometrically well-defined dense thin-film (0.8-2 mu m thickness) electrode, fabricated as a symmetric cell.
Titulo: Identifying the Origin of the Limiting Process in a Double Perovskite PrBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.5Fe0.5O5+δ Thin-Film Electrode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In combination with density functional theory (DFT) and molecular dynamics (MD) simulations, experiments provided an insight into the operating mechanism of the SOFC material tested at an open-circuit voltage.
Titulo: Identifying the Origin of the Limiting Process in a Double Perovskite PrBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.5Fe0.5O5+δ Thin-Film Electrode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The dense thin-film electrode of PBSCF showed a thickness-dependent electrochemical performance, suggesting bulk diffusion limitation.
Titulo: Identifying the Origin of the Limiting Process in a Double Perovskite PrBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.5Fe0.5O5+δ Thin-Film Electrode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: To understand the origin of this diffusion-limiting electrochemical performance, DFT calculations were utilized to calculate the surface (gamma) and oxygen vacancy formation (E-OV) energies.
Titulo: Identifying the Origin of the Limiting Process in a Double Perovskite PrBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.5Fe0.5O5+δ Thin-Film Electrode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: For example, E-OV in the Pr plane (190 kJ/mol) of PBSCF was measured to be lower than that of the BaSr plane (E-OV = 297 kJ/mol).
Titulo: Identifying the Origin of the Limiting Process in a Double Perovskite PrBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.5Fe0.5O5+δ Thin-Film Electrode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In addition, oxygen vacancies were difficult to be created in the BaSr/CoFe terminal surface (E-OV = 341.6 kJ/mol) as compared to other terminal surfaces.
Titulo: Identifying the Origin of the Limiting Process in a Double Perovskite PrBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.5Fe0.5O5+δ Thin-Film Electrode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: MD simulations further elaborated on the nature of cation disordering in the surface and subsurface regions, consequently leading segregation of the Ba cations to the surface, which is a known phenomenon in such double perovskite materials.
Titulo: Identifying the Origin of the Limiting Process in a Double Perovskite PrBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.5Fe0.5O5+δ Thin-Film Electrode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Because of cation disordering and segregation of Ba species, the oxygen anion diffusivity (similar to 10(-12) cm(2) s(-1)), calculated from MD, in the near-surface region was observed to be 2 orders of magnitude lesser than that of the bulk (D = 2.98 X 10(-10)
Titulo: Identifying the Origin of the Limiting Process in a Double Perovskite PrBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.5Fe0.5O5+δ Thin-Film Electrode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Titulo: Identifying the Origin of the Limiting Process in a Double Perovskite PrBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.5Fe0.5O5+δ Thin-Film Electrode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
